column1: Atmospheric CO2 concentrations (ppm) derived from in situ air measurements
at Mauna Loa, Observatory, Hawaii: Latitude 19.5°N Longitude 155.6°W Elevation 3397m
These data are a compilation of the latest archived monthly MLO dataset and preliminary
values after the end date of the archived monthly dataset. This dataset also includes any
preliminary daily and weekly values after the preliminary monthly values.
Mauna Loa carbon dioxide data from the most recent month is preliminary and subject to
subsequence updates to account for retrospective calibration and quality control.
See scrippsco2.ucsd.edu for data that has passed these routine quality checks and updates.
The datasets are archived once a month on the scrippsco2.ucsd.edu website and on the
archive database site of the UCSD library library.ucsd.edu/dc/collection/bb3381541w.
Source: R. F. Keeling, S. J. Walker, S. C. Piper and A. F. Bollenbacher
Scripps CO2 Program ( http://scrippsco2.ucsd.edu )
Scripps Institution of Oceanography (SIO)
University of California
La Jolla, California USA 92093-0244
Status of data and correspondence:

about the data should be directed to Dr. Ralph Keeling (rkeeling@ucsd.edu), Stephen Walker
(sjwalker@ucsd.edu) and Stephen Piper (scpiper@ucsd.edu), Scripps CO2 Program.

The data file below contains 6 columns.  Columns 1, 3, & 5 are dates as decimal years.
Column 2 (co2_dy), Column 4 (co2_wk), and Column 6 (co2_mn) give daily, weekly and monthly
Mauna Loa CO2 concentrations in micro-mol CO2 per mole (ppm), reported on the 2012
SIO manometric mole fraction scale.
Column 2 (co2_dy) gives daily CO2 Concentration values after the last monthly date, and
Column 4 (co2_wk) gives weekly CO2 Concentration values after the last monthly date
The daily averages have been screened to eliminate local influences such as the impacts
of downslope vegetation or volcanic fumaroles on the record.
The weekly values have been adjusted to 12:00 hours at middle day of each weekly period
The monthly values have been adjusted to 24:00 hours on the 15th of each month.
Column 1, 3, and 5 are dates as decimal years
Column 2 (co2_dy), Column 4 (co2_wk) and Column 6 (co2_mn) below give the daily, weekly,
and monthly Mauna Loa CO2 concentrations in micro-mol CO2 per mole (ppm), reported on the
2012 SIO manometric mole fraction scale.
Missing values are denoted by NaN.
CO2 concentrations are measured on the '12' calibration scale
